Class GameElementTracker

Direct Known Subclasses:

public class GameElementTracker
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<GameElement>

Template for a GameElement collection handler.

This class represents a list of GameElements. It notifies to its subscribers when an element is created or removed. In that way, we can asynchronously update the state of any object that listens to this changes.

It would be useful in case we would like to create a statistics or scores punctuation system in real time for example.

Author:
Luis Carlos Mateos
